parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the secondary air injection system can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to power loss and potentially causing accidents.
Failure of the cam tower seal can cause oil to leak onto the exhaust manifold, leading to a fire hazard and potentially causing engine failure.
symptoms: Oil leak onto the exhaust manifold
oil leak on the heat shield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the fuel pump can cause delayed starting, difficulty starting, and potentially lead to complete power loss while driving.
symptoms: engine turning over but not starting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Issues with the crankshaft and camshaft can cause engine knocking, poor gas mileage, and potentially lead to engine failure.
Power steering fluid leak can cause the steering wheel to shake and make it difficult to control the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents.
Engine stalling can cause loss of power and potentially lead to accidents.
The failure of the steering rack can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the intermediate steering shaft can cause abnormal noise, vibration, or loss of steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal noise coming from the steering wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can prevent the driver from alerting other road users to potential hazards, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Horn does not work when a road hazard is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driveshaft or wheel bearing can cause vibration, noise, or loss of control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vibration issue coming from the bottom
wheel bearing had to be replaced
front end alignment was way out of whack.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: seal popped on the steering arm and fluid started leaking out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air injection pump can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: especially when merging into traffic; the engine light comes on; the air injection pump values show water or moisture.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ECU software issue can cause poor fuel economy, decreased performance, and difficulty starting the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle has poor fuel economy
and shifting issues; the fuel trims are way into negative; the ALC density percentage is too high.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch system can cause the vehicle to be unable to shift into gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the backup camera can cause a safety risk, particularly when reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or pedestrians behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The backup camera cuts in and out
shows a blue screen when put in reverse
and is more prone to failure in rainy conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rodent damage to the engine wiring harness can cause engine failure, short circuits, and other safety risks, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rodents chew through the wiring harness
causing damage to the engine and electrical systems

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Secondary Air Injection System Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the secondary air injection system pump can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to safety risks, particularly when driving on the freeway.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Intermittent Engine, TRAC Control, and 4WD LO Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the engine, TRAC control, and 4WD LO lights can cause confusion and safety risks, particularly when driving in hazardous conditions.
symptoms: and 4WD LO lights flash intermittently while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the horn can cause a safety risk, particularly when trying to alert other drivers or pedestrians.
symptoms: The horn stops working or works intermittently
and may be a common issue with this truck model.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock actuator can cause inconvenience and safety risks, particularly when trying to lock or unlock the doors.
symptoms: The door lock actuator fails to work
causing the doors to unlock or lock randomly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause a significant safety risk, potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
